The paper discusses the use of Intrinsically Motivated Goal Exploration Processes for skill acquisition in robots, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of deep representation learning for feature extraction from visual input, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper presents results from a real-world robotic setup, which involves control systems (cs.SY).
